    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="368"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.911/16.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 619.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my telegrams of February 6 (1 p.m.
                    and 2 p.m.) in regard to abusive articles concerning the Legation published in
                    the newspaper “Cuba,” I have the honor to transmit herewith enclosed copies and
                    translations of the two articles in question.<note n="1" xml:id="d368fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> Judging from the tenor of the articles already published, it
                    is to be presumed that they will be followed by others of a similar nature.</p>
                <p>The Department is in possession of the facts concerning past offenses of this
                    newspaper in its attacks upon Mr. Gibson last August and upon the President at a
                    later date. I therefore deem it superfluous to enter into a discussion of the
                    matter, but venture to confirm my earnest recommendation already made that I be
                    authorized to present a formal request to the Cuban Government that action be
                    taken against this newspaper for criminal libel.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. M. Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
